Sentencas: The sinterability of (Y(0.08)Sr(0.92))(1-x)TiO(3-delta) samples decreases slightly with increasing A-site deficiency level (x).

Sentencas: The ionic conductivity of (Y(0.08)Sr(0.92))(1-x)TiO(3-delta) samples increases while the electronic conductivity decreases with increasing A-site deficient amount The defect chemistry analysis indicates that the introduction of A-site deficiency results in not only the increase of oxygen vacancy concentration but also the decrease of Ti(3+)-ion concentration.
